> **Architecture note:** AI synthesis is orchestrated through N8N, not Supabase Edge Functions. N8N handles the multi-call synthesis chains (especially MRA, which requires sequential Claude calls), merge field population into Google Docs templates, PDF packaging, storage back to Supabase, and delivery triggers. Supabase Edge Functions may be used for lightweight, synchronous AI calls (e.g., Agency Snapshot synthesis) but N8N is the primary synthesis engine.

