## 3. Data Model

### MRA Content Tables (Already Live in Supabase)

> **Important:** The 125 MRA checkpoints × 5 AE Ladder stages = 500 stage-calibrated checkpoint definitions are already live in Supabase. These are not defined in a frontend config file — they live in Supabase tables that the assessment reads at runtime. Each checkpoint has a stage-calibrated "what good looks like" definition for every AE Ladder stage (Rising through Arriving). These tables also feed the AI synthesis layer via N8N — the report generation workflow pulls the relevant definitions and uses them in Claude prompt construction. Vector stores for report embeddings are also already set up in Supabase. No build work is needed on MRA content — only verification that the wiring is reading the correct tables correctly.

