## 5. User Stories

**US-001** — As a beta founder, I want to complete the Agency Snapshot and immediately receive an AI-synthesized readback of my business, so that I can see my business as a strategic advisor would see it.

**US-002** — As a beta founder, I want to be able to split the MRA (125Q) across two sessions without losing my progress, so that I can complete it honestly without feeling rushed.

**US-003** — As a beta founder, I want to select my 3P capability areas and have the system enforce the limit (3 Prioritize, 3 Plant, 3 Progressively Iterate), so that I am forced to prioritize rather than trying to fix everything.

**US-004** — As a beta founder, I want the Sprint Launch Document to be auto-generated when I lock my sprint, so that I have a professional artifact to share with my team in our alignment session.

**US-005** — As a beta founder, I want my maturity scores to update automatically as my team completes milestones, so that my dashboard reflects real execution progress without manual score management.

**US-006** — As a beta founder, I want to resume incomplete assessments from where I left off, so that I do not have to restart a 125-question audit.

**US-007** — As a beta founder, I want my AE Ladder stage placement to inform the MRA — so that the 125 checkpoints are calibrated to where I actually am, not what an industry average looks like.

**US-008** — As a founder, I want to open the Status Tracker during a team stand-up and hide sensitive founder-level initiatives before sharing my screen, so that the team sees only the milestones relevant to their work without exposing strategic data I'm not ready to share.

**US-009** — As a platform admin (London), I want to control which features are unlocked for the beta cohort on a per-week basis, so that I can manage the program rollout without code changes.

**US-010** — As a beta founder, I want to download my MRA report as a PDF, so that I can share it with advisors and reference it offline.

