## 6. Functional Requirements

### FR-001 — User Authentication
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Auth
- Users must register with email + password via Supabase Auth
- Session persists across browser refreshes via Supabase JWT
- All routes behind `/app/*` redirect to `/sign-in` if unauthenticated
- On sign-up, a `profiles` row is automatically created via Supabase trigger
- Acceptance: User can sign up, log in, refresh browser, and remain authenticated

### FR-002 — Beta Tier Gating
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Tier Gating
- Beta users (is_beta = true) can only access features unlocked for their current cohort week
- `beta_cohort_week` on the `profiles` table controls access
- Feature gates are checked from `beta_feature_gates` table; features with `unlocked = true` AND `week_number <= user.beta_cohort_week` are accessible
- Locked features render a "Coming in Program Week X" state — not a 404
- Admin can update `beta_cohort_week` for all beta users to advance feature access
- Acceptance: User cannot navigate to MRA page when `beta_cohort_week < 5`

### FR-003 — Agency Snapshot
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Foundations — Snapshot
- Five input sections: Economic Foundation, Revenue Model, Market Footprint, Delivery Architecture, Team Structure
- All fields auto-save to Supabase as user types (debounced, 2s)
- "Generate Synthesis" button triggers `generate-snapshot-synthesis` edge function
- Loading state shown during synthesis generation (skeleton/spinner with copy: "Synthesizing your current state model...")
- Synthesis displayed on Dashboard tab as a structured readback
- If snapshot is incomplete when synthesis is requested, highlight missing required fields
- Acceptance: User completes all sections, clicks Generate, waits ≤30s, sees AI readback

### FR-004 — AE Ladder Assessment
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Diagnostics — AE Ladder
- 19 questions across 5 dimensions (Financial Health, Client Base, Operations, Team, Stewardship)
- Question content loaded from `config/ae-ladder-content.ts`
- Progress indicator shows "Question X of 19"
- Responses auto-saved to Supabase after each question (no risk of loss)
- On final submission: stage placement calculated deterministically from scores
- Report generation triggered automatically (`generate-ae-ladder-report` edge function)
- Results Dashboard shows: stage badge, dimension score breakdown, active roadblocks, upcoming challenges
- Stage Profile tab shows full report text
- Stage Guide auto-delivered as secondary content
- Acceptance: 19 questions completed → stage placement shown within 60s

### FR-005 — Maturity and Readiness Audit (MRA)
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Diagnostics — MRA
- 125 checkpoints across 5 dimensions × 25 capability areas × 5 checkpoints each
- Checkpoints stage-calibrated from AE Ladder placement (questions ask "does your business have X at your stage?")
- Split-session support: auto-saves after every checkpoint; resume from last answered on return
- Completion percentage shown at top: "87 of 125 checkpoints completed"
- "Assessment Approach Note" shown before starting: "Answer based on how your business actually operates on an ordinary week — not its best week, not what you're building toward."
- On completion: MRA scores calculated, `generate-mra-report` edge function triggered
- Results page: Act 1 (executive narrative), Act 2 (dimension breakdown with scores), Act 3 (cross-dimensional patterns)
- 3P priority tags shown on capability areas (AI-suggested; founder can adjust)
- Maturity score + Readiness score shown prominently on dashboard after completion
- Acceptance: 125 checkpoints completed → full report generated within 90s

### FR-006 — Clarity Compass
**Priority:** P1 | **Feature:** Foundations — Clarity Compass
- Four input levels: Ultimate Vision + 12-month + 24-month + 36-month horizons
- Each horizon captures: qualitative picture, quantitative targets, what it feels like, what it's optimizing for
- All inputs auto-save to Supabase
- "Confirm Horizons" action locks the declaration and unlocks Horizon Declaration in Quarter Map
- Dashboard tab shows a synthesis view of all declared horizons
- Acceptance: User declares all horizons → Horizon Declaration appears as available in Quarter Map

### FR-007 — Growth Velocity Calculator
**Priority:** P1 | **Feature:** Foundations — GV Calculator
- Input: current revenue, team size, target revenue scenario, horizon (12/24/36 months)
- Output: surfaced pressure families at that growth level (6 pressure families defined in methodology)
- Scenario Planner: side-by-side comparison of 2+ scenarios
- Results saved to Supabase
- Acceptance: User inputs current state + target → pressure family analysis renders

### FR-008 — Quarter Map (3P Capability Selection)
**Priority:** P0 | **Feature:** Pro Suite — Planning
- **Orientation tab:** Shows current AE Ladder stage, MRA scores summary, and "what this quarter requires"
- **Strategic Horizons tab:** Reads from Clarity Compass + MRA synthesis; shows roadmap review synthesis
- **12-Month Plan tab:** Execution Sequencer — platform-proposed quarterly sprint sequence with contextual override fields
- **Quarter Map / Current Quarter Focus tab:** The 3P selector
