## 7. Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance
- Page load time (authenticated): < 2s on standard broadband
- Claude API report generation: < 60s for Snapshot/AE Ladder, < 90s for MRA (show progress state)
- Status Tracker milestone update: < 500ms round trip to Supabase
- Auto-save (all input forms): debounce 2s, save to Supabase within 3s of last keystroke
- Sprint Board load: < 1.5s even with 9 capability cards and 20+ milestones

### Security
- All user data protected by Supabase RLS — no user can read another user's data
- Claude API key never exposed to client — all AI calls via Supabase Edge Functions
- Environment variables for all secrets — no hardcoded keys in codebase
- Auth tokens validated server-side on all Edge Function calls

### Accessibility
- All interactive elements keyboard-accessible
- Color is not the sole indicator of status (icons + labels alongside color)
- Form fields include descriptive labels
- Note: Full WCAG 2.1 AA compliance is a post-beta target, not a beta requirement

### Scalability
- Architecture handles 100 concurrent users without changes (Supabase scales automatically)
- Claude API calls are stateless and parallelizable
- Data model supports unlimited sprints, assessments, and initiatives per user

### Reliability
- Zero tolerance for data loss: all input data saved to Supabase before any navigation
- Assessment progress preserved across browser crashes via auto-save
- If Claude API call fails: display error state with retry button; do not lose input data

