## 11. Edge Cases and Error Handling

| Scenario | Expected Behavior |
|----------|------------------|
| Claude API times out during report generation | Show error state: "Report generation timed out. Your data is saved — click Retry to try again." Log error to Supabase. |
| User loses internet mid-assessment | Auto-save fires on every response; on reconnect, resume from last saved checkpoint |
| MRA submitted before AE Ladder completed | Block MRA access; show prompt: "Complete the AE Ladder Assessment first — it calibrates your MRA checkpoints." |
| Sprint locked before Quarter Map completed | Block Sprint Lock; prompt to complete Quarter Map first |
| User tries to add 4th area to Prioritize bucket | Button/drag target disabled; toast: "Prioritize has 3 areas. Move one to Plant or Progressively Iterate to make room." |
| Milestone marked complete with no checkpoint mapping | Update milestone status; skip maturity score recalculation; log warning |
| Beta user tries to access Week 6 feature in Week 3 | Show gated state: "This feature unlocks in Program Week 6. Your coach will let you know when it's time." |
| Auto-save fails (Supabase error) | Show inline warning: "Changes not saved — check your connection." Retry automatically every 30s. |
| Synthesis generation called with incomplete inputs | Validate required fields before triggering Claude call; highlight missing fields |
| User retakes AE Ladder | Create new `ae_ladder_assessments` record; use most recent for MRA calibration; old records preserved |

